    //**javascript**//
      localStorage is an HTML5 API
      to store data to browser. it accepts Strings only
      You will often use 3 methods only
      localStorage.setItem() // to store data to localStorage 
      localStorage.getItem() // to get some data from localStorage
      localStorage.clear() // to clear the localStorage

      /* Examples */

      localStorage.setItem('firstName', 'hello this is my name'); << دي تتعمل منفصلة لكل ايتيم ؟ 
      // yep

      localStorage.getItem('firstName') // Returns 'hello this is my name'

      localStorage.clear() <<هنا مسح الفريست نيم ف لما جيت تعمل جيت تحتها ف ان ديفايند صح كدا ؟
        // localStorage.clear() clears all localStorage
        so yes, it deletes firstName. but if therer were other keys, for example 'lastName'. they would also be removed okay
      localStorage.getItem('firstName') // undefined 

      // بس كدة

      //event = event || window.event  << ليه كتبت او .؟وبيتسيف
    // المتصفحات ممكن ميعرفوش اني اقصد الابفنت ف بضطر اقلهم ان ده window.event
    تمام فهمتك 
     event.preventDefault() << دا بيمنع الفعل الحقيقي او الطبيعي الي بيحصل ؟وبيتسيف
     yep, for exam[ple]. forms by default get submitted when you submit them. if I don't want that, I can use event.preventDefault()
     another example, anchor tags "<a href="somelink"></a>" go to their links when they are clicked. I can disable this behaviour by using event.preventDefault()
    do you understand? yes ^_^ طب ثانية يعني مثلا التاج دا خليته ميروحش لي لنكات طب وقتها ايه فايدته ما اكتبه مثلا في برجراف ؟



